                            <comment id="12897465" author="techhusky" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2010 22:29:24 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;+1  While this requirement makes it very clear that the cache can be distributed, it complicates configuration for the simple and probably most common case.  If this can be done without breaking product derivations and such, I think we should do it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12897469" author="drwoods" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2010 22:31:57 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 Sounds like a good usability improvement.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
